ExecDesc.value: Microsoft Windows Font Library File Buffer Overflow

EngDesc.value: A buffer overflow vulnerability exists in Microsoft Windows operating system. The vulnerability is due to an input validation error when the kernel parses a .FON font file. Attackers can exploit this vulnerability by enticing a user to open a malformed .fon font file. Successful exploitation of this vulnerability would result in the execution of arbitrary code within the security privileges of the Windows kernel.
